visualeditor:
The name of the VisualEditor extension.
{{Identical|VisualEditor}}
visualeditor-aliennode-tooltip: Tooltip for items that VisualEditor cannot edit
visualeditor-align-desc-right:
Used in visual diffs to describe automatically that an image was aligned to the right.

See also {{msg-mw|visualeditor-changedesc-align}}{{Identical|Right}}
visualeditor-alignablecontextitem-title:
Title for the context item for alignable nodes
{{Identical|Alignment}}
visualeditor-changedesc-link-added:
Description of a link being added.

Values:
* $1 – Link target
visualeditor-changedesc-link-removed:
Description of a link being removed.

Values:
* $1 – Link target
visualeditor-changedesc-list-indent: Description of a list item's indentation being increased
visualeditor-changedesc-list-outdent: Description of a List item's indentation being decreased
visualeditor-changedesc-list-style-inden:
Description of a list item that is just plain indentation (done using : in wikitext and translated to
in HTML).
visualeditor-changedesc-textstyle-added:
Description of a text style being added to some text

Values
* $1 – The text style (e.g. 'Bold')
visualeditor-changedesc-textstyle-remove:
Description of a text style being removed from some text

Values
* $1 – The text style (e.g. 'Bold')
visualeditor-changedesc-unknown:
Fallback description of an attribute value change for visual diffing which can't be otherwise described, if no specific i18n exists for that kind of change.

Values:
* $1 – Attribute name, like 'lang' or 'dir'
{{Related|Visualeditor-changedesc}}
visualeditor-changedir: Label for tool to change directionality
visualeditor-changedir-tool-ltr: Label for tool to change rendered directionality to LTR
visualeditor-changedir-tool-rtl: Label for tool to change rendered directionality to RTL
visualeditor-clearbutton-tooltip:
Tooltip text for the remove button. Clears whatever formatting is associated with the context popup.
{{Identical|Remove}}
visualeditor-clipboard-copy-fail: Message shown when copying to clipboard failed.
visualeditor-clipboard-copy-success: Message shown when copying to clipboard worked.
visualeditor-clipboard-paste-special: Label for paste as plain text command
visualeditor-collab-copy-title: Title for the dialog that provides the collaboration URL for the user to share
visualeditor-collab-dialog-privacy: Information about privacy in collaboration sessions
visualeditor-collab-dialog-sessionend: Information about the lifetime of collaboration sessions
visualeditor-collab-dialog-sharing: Information about how changes are shared in collaboration sessions
visualeditor-collab-dialog-summary-host: Summary for the collaboration dialog when hosting a session
visualeditor-collab-dialog-summary-join: Summary for the collaboration dialog when joining a session
visualeditor-collab-hostbutton-label: Label for the button to host a new collaboration session
visualeditor-collab-joinbutton-label: Label for the button to join an existing collaboration session
visualeditor-collab-url-mismatch: Error message when the collaboration URL does not match the page URL
visualeditor-collab-url-placeholder: Placeholder for the TextInput where the user enters a collaboration URL
visualeditor-collab-url-prompt: Prompt for the TextInput where the user enters a collaboration URL
visualeditor-collab-user-placeholder:
Placeholder name for a user when they joing a collaboration session.

Values:
* $1 – User ID, a small auto-incrementing number starting at 1.
visualeditor-command-dialog-cancel: Label for the command to close a window and discard its changes
visualeditor-command-dialog-confirm: Label for the command to close a window and make its changes
visualeditor-command-dialog-focus-contex: Label for the command to move focus to the contextual popup
visualeditor-commentannotationcontextite: Label for the comment button in the comment annotation inspector
visualeditor-completionwidget-noresults: Label shown when the completion widget has no results
visualeditor-content-select-all:
Label for select all command.
{{Identical|Select all}}
visualeditor-contextitemwidget-label-clo:
Label for the close button on a context item on mobile.
{{identical|Close}}
visualeditor-contextitemwidget-label-vie: Label for the view action on a context item, when the surface is in read-only mode.
visualeditor-debugbar-close:
Label for the button to dismiss the debug toolbar.
{{Identical|Close}}
visualeditor-debugbar-inputdebug: Label for the button in the debug toolbar to run keyboard input in debug mode.
visualeditor-debugbar-logrange:
Label for the button in the debug toolbar to output the current selection to the JavaScript console.
{{doc-important|"Log" is a verb here. Translate as "log the selected (text)", and NOT as "the log (that was) selected".}}
visualeditor-debugbar-showmodel: Label for the button in the debug toolbar to show the document model.
visualeditor-debugbar-showtransactions: Label for the button in the debug toolbar to show the transaction history.
visualeditor-debugbar-startfilibuster: Label for the button in the debug toolbar to begin the input response trace debugger (extremely detailed logging of the editor's behavior).
visualeditor-debugbar-stopfilibuster: Label for the button in the debug toolbar to stop the input response trace debugger.
visualeditor-debugbar-testsquasher:
Label for the button in the debug toolbar to test the transaction squasher.

Alternative words for "squasher" could be "compactor", "combiner", or "aggregator". See [[phab:T202465#4557136]] for an explanation of what the transaction squasher does.
visualeditor-debugbar-updatemodel: Label for the button in the debug toolbar to update the shown document model as it changes.
visualeditor-dialog-command-help-title:
Title for keyboard shortcuts help dialog.
{{Identical|Keyboard shortcut}}
visualeditor-dialog-language-auto-direct:
Label text for button to make language direction automatic.
{{Identical|Automatic}}
visualeditor-dialog-language-search-titl:
Title for language search dialog
{{Identical|Select language}}
visualeditor-dialog-table-caption:
Label for caption toggle in table dialog.
{{Identical|Caption}}
visualeditor-diff-moved-down: Description of an item that has been moved down the page for visual diffing.
visualeditor-diff-moved-up: Description of an item that has been moved up the page for visual diffing.
visualeditor-diff-no-changes: Label displayed in the diff view when no net changes have been made.
visualeditor-diff-timed-out: Label displayed in the diff view if the diff took too long to compute accurately.
visualeditor-dimensionswidget-height: Label for the height field in the dimensions properties.
visualeditor-dimensionswidget-px:
{{optional}}
Label for the dimensions properties denoting pixel units.
visualeditor-dimensionswidget-times:
{{optional}}
Label for the dimensions properties denoting 'by', as in width x height.
visualeditor-dimensionswidget-width: Label for the width field in the dimensions properties.
visualeditor-find-and-replace-diacritic: Label for diacritic insensitive toggle in find and replace
visualeditor-find-and-replace-done:
Label for button to finish using the find and replace dialog
{{Identical|Done}}
visualeditor-find-and-replace-find-text:
Label for find text in find and replace
{{Identical|Find}}
visualeditor-find-and-replace-invalid-re: Inline error message shown for an invalid regular expression
visualeditor-find-and-replace-match-case:
Label for match case toggle in find and replace.

{{Identical|Match case}}
visualeditor-find-and-replace-next-butto:
Label for find next result button in find and replace
{{Identical|Find next}}
visualeditor-find-and-replace-previous-b: Label for find previous result button in find and replace
visualeditor-find-and-replace-regular-ex:
Label for regular expression toggle in find and replace
{{Identical|Regular expression}}
visualeditor-find-and-replace-replace-al: Label for replace all button in find and replace
visualeditor-find-and-replace-replace-bu:
Label for replace button in find and replace
{{Identical|Replace}}
visualeditor-find-and-replace-replace-te:
Label for replace text in find and replace
{{Identical|Replace}}
visualeditor-find-and-replace-results:
Label for find results showing how many results were found ($2), and which one is currently highlighted ($1)
{{Identical|Of}}
visualeditor-find-and-replace-word: Label for whole word toggle in find and replace
visualeditor-formatdropdown-format-block: Item in the formatting dropdown for block quote text. A block quote is a quotation which is a whole paragraph, or several paragraphs.
visualeditor-formatdropdown-format-headi:
Item in the generic formatting dropdown for a level 1 heading.
{{Identical|Heading}}

Item in the generic formatting dropdown for a level 2 heading.
{{Identical|Heading}}

Item in the generic formatting dropdown for a level 3 heading.
{{Identical|Heading}}

Item in the generic formatting dropdown for a level 4 heading.
{{Identical|Heading}}

Item in the generic formatting dropdown for a level 5 heading.
{{Identical|Heading}}

Item in the generic formatting dropdown for a level 6 heading.
{{Identical|Heading}}
visualeditor-help-tool:
Title of popup tool in toolbar that provides help information.
{{Identical|Help}}
visualeditor-historybutton-redo-tooltip:
Tooltip text for the redo button.
{{Identical|Redo}}
visualeditor-historybutton-undo-tooltip:
Tooltip text for the undo button.
{{Identical|Undo}}
visualeditor-horizontalrule-tooltip: Tooltip text for the button that inserts a horizontal rule, a horizontal line that acts as a separator.
visualeditor-indentationbutton-indent-to: Tooltip text for list indent button
visualeditor-indentationbutton-outdent-t: Tooltip text for list outdent button
visualeditor-inspector-remove-tooltip:
Tooltip text for the button to remove an annotation in an inspector.
{{Identical|Remove}}
visualeditor-key-meta:
{{Optional}}
The common identifier of the meta key. Used for building keyboard shortcut messages.
visualeditor-key-right:
The common identifier of the right arrow key. Used for building keyboard shortcut messages.
{{Related|Visualeditor-key}}
visualeditor-key-space:
The common identifier of the space bar. Used for building keyboard shortcut messages.
{{Related|Visualeditor-key}}
visualeditor-key-up:
The common identifier of the up arrow key. Used for building keyboard shortcut messages.
{{Related|Visualeditor-key}}
visualeditor-language-search-input-place: Placeholder text for language search widget.
visualeditor-languageannotation-descript:
Description of a language annotation

* $1 - Language autonym

{{optional}}

Description of a language annotation with overridden directionality

* $1 - Language autonym
* $2 - Overridden direction (either LTR or RTL)
visualeditor-languagecontext-remove: Title for the remove language button on the language context popup
visualeditor-languageinspector-title:
Title of the language inspector dialog.
{{Identical|Language}}
visualeditor-languageinspector-widget-ch: Label for the language change button in the language inspector widget.
visualeditor-languageinspector-widget-la:
Label for the language inspector widget, to denote the text direction of the current element (left-to-right or right-to-left).
{{Identical|Direction}}

Label for the language inspector widget, to denote the current block language code.
{{Identical|Language code}}

Label for the language inspector widget, to denote the current block language.
{{Identical|Language}}
visualeditor-linkcontext-label-change: Label for the change text button. This sets the current selection to the entire contents of the link, so it can be easily edited.
visualeditor-linkcontext-label-fallback: Fallback for the preview of a link label if it's not displayable as text
visualeditor-linkcontext-label-label:
Label for the "text" field of a link
{{Identical|Text}}
visualeditor-linkcontext-remove: Title for the remove link button on the link context popup
visualeditor-linkinspector-title:
Title of the link inspector dialog when viewing a link in read-only mode.
{{Identical|Link}}
visualeditor-linkinspector-title-add: Title of the link inspector dialog when adding a link.
visualeditor-linkinspector-title-edit: Title of the link inspector dialog when editing a link.
visualeditor-listbutton-bullet-tooltip: Tooltip text for the bullet list button
visualeditor-listbutton-check-tooltip: Tooltip text for the check list button. A "check list" is todo-style list with checkboxes.
visualeditor-listbutton-number-tooltip: Tooltip text for the numbered list button
visualeditor-mediasizewidget-label-defau: An error label notifying the user the size inputs are invalid.
visualeditor-mediasizewidget-label-scale:
Label for the media size widget scale section indicating a scaling of an image based on thumbnail size.

Translated in conjunction with {{msg-mw|Visualeditor-mediasizewidget-label-scale}}: "Scale ____ % of thumbnail size", meaning the scale of the displayed image shall be x% of the default thumbnail size.
visualeditor-mediasizewidget-sizeoptions:
Label for the media size widget size select for custom size.
{{Identical|Custom}}

Label for the media size widget size select for default size.
{{Identical|Default}}

Label for the media size widget size select for scaled size. The expected input is a percentage - see [[MediaWiki:Visualeditor-mediasizewidget-label-scale/en]].
{{Identical|Scale}}
visualeditor-rebase-client-author-name:
Label for the input to set or change the user's account display name.
{{Identical|Name}}
visualeditor-rebase-client-connecting: Title of progress bar shown while waiting to connect to the rebase server
visualeditor-rebase-client-document-crea: Label for button to create or edit a document by name
visualeditor-rebase-corrupted-document-e: Error message shown when a document is corrupted on the rebase server.
visualeditor-rebase-corrupted-document-t: Title for the corrupted document alert
visualeditor-rebase-missing-document-err: Error message shown when a document is missing on the rebase server
visualeditor-rebase-missing-document-tit: Title for the missing document alert
visualeditor-shortcuts-dialog: Heading for dialog window control shortcuts
visualeditor-slug-insert: Label for slug to insert paragraph on an otherwise unreachable line
visualeditor-specialcharacter-button-too:
Tooltip text for the insert character button.

visualeditor-table-context-row: Accessibility label for the menu of options for a table row.
visualeditor-table-contextitem-propertie:
Label for the properties button in the table context
{{Identical|Property}}
visualeditor-table-contextitem-selection: Label for the select cells button in the table context
Label for the select cell contents button in the table context
visualeditor-table-delete-col:
Label for delete column tool

* $1 is the number of columns
visualeditor-table-delete-row:
Label for delete row tool

* $1 is the number of rows

visualeditor-table-format-header: Label for table cell header tool

Label for insert row above tool

visualeditor-table-merge-cells: Label for merge cells context item

Label for the merge cells button

visualeditor-table-move-col-before: Label for move column before tool

{{optional}}
The dimensions of a table selection.

* $2 – Row count (height).
